WEBVTT

00:00:42.250 --> 00:00:45.962
‚ÄéSPOOKY IN LOVE

00:01:39.098 --> 00:01:40.183
‚ÄéCEO CHEON YEO-RI

00:01:47.315 --> 00:01:49.400
‚ÄéEPISODE 2

00:01:52.654 --> 00:01:55.740
‚ÄéWhy do you run away ‚Äéwhenever we meet, Ms. Cheon?

00:01:55.824 --> 00:01:58.618
‚ÄéI wasn't running away. I was avoiding you.

00:01:58.701 --> 00:02:01.788
‚ÄéWhy avoid me like I'm some kind of virus?

00:02:02.747 --> 00:02:04.124
‚ÄéOkay, fine. So you avoided me.

00:02:04.207 --> 00:02:06.459
‚ÄéWhy do that ‚Äéif you're not guilty of anything?

00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:09.254
‚ÄéPeople who aren't guilty ‚Äécan avoid others if they want.

00:02:09.337 --> 00:02:11.297
‚ÄéOh, so you ignore everyone to start with?

00:02:11.965 --> 00:02:13.508
‚ÄéTo be honest, I couldn't stand you.

00:02:14.425 --> 00:02:15.718
‚ÄéYou left a terrible first impression.

00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:17.679
‚ÄéI'd say you're just as bad in that aspect.

00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:24.519
‚ÄéSo what is it that you want to know?

00:02:25.270 --> 00:02:27.647
‚ÄéYou reported the body on Mt. Haewang, ‚Äédidn't you?

00:02:29.107 --> 00:02:30.942
‚ÄéYou caught the culprit and found the body.

00:02:31.025 --> 00:02:32.485
‚ÄéDoes it matter who reported it?

00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.487
‚ÄéThere could be more than one culprit,

00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:37.407
‚Äéand it's too suspicious ‚Äéthat you knew where the body was.

00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:38.491
‚ÄéAre you saying

00:02:39.159 --> 00:02:40.827
‚Äéthat I'm the accomplice?

00:02:40.910 --> 00:02:43.079
‚ÄéIf something feels off, ‚Äéisn't it best to cover all bases?

00:02:43.163 --> 00:02:44.956
‚ÄéDelusion must come ‚Äéwith being a prosecutor.

00:02:45.039 --> 00:02:46.875
‚ÄéLet's say I'm here to check facts.

00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:50.003
‚ÄéHow did you know the body was there?

00:02:52.922 --> 00:02:54.883
‚ÄéYou seem to have asked ‚Äéall you wanted to know.

00:02:57.302 --> 00:02:58.219
‚ÄéPlease leave.

00:02:58.720 --> 00:03:01.431
‚ÄéWhat's the point of asking ‚Äéwhen you didn't answer a single one?

00:03:02.765 --> 00:03:04.058
‚ÄéTell me just one thing.

00:03:04.642 --> 00:03:06.019
‚ÄéHow did you know the body was there?

00:03:08.354 --> 00:03:09.230
‚ÄéI was told.

00:03:11.774 --> 00:03:12.817
‚ÄéBy whom?

00:03:13.484 --> 00:03:15.486
‚Äé-By a ghost. ‚Äé-What?

00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:17.822
‚ÄéAre you kidding me right now?

00:03:19.198 --> 00:03:20.909
‚ÄéWhy ask if you won't believe me?

00:03:20.992 --> 00:03:23.161
‚ÄéAre you a psychic medium or a shaman

00:03:23.244 --> 00:03:25.121
‚Äé-for a ghost to tell you that? ‚Äé-Ms. Cheon.

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:41.012
‚ÄéDid I hit the nail on the head?

00:03:41.095 --> 00:03:42.513
‚ÄéNow I feel bad for no reason.

00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:45.558
‚ÄéHey!

00:03:48.811 --> 00:03:50.813
‚ÄéI can't believe I'm seeing this.

00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.607
‚ÄéWhat are you doing in a place like this?

00:03:52.690 --> 00:03:55.068
‚ÄéI come to such places often, ‚Äéto enforce search warrants.

00:03:57.237 --> 00:03:59.614
‚ÄéWhat do you think? ‚ÄéTotally luxurious, right?

00:03:59.697 --> 00:04:02.533
‚ÄéThe owner of this hotel ‚Äéis my future cousin-in-law.

00:04:02.617 --> 00:04:05.370
‚ÄéWant me to pull some strings ‚Äéand get you a membership?

00:04:06.120 --> 00:04:08.706
‚ÄéYou really must have a thing for hotels.

00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:11.668
‚ÄéJang Eun-ju disappeared from a hotel too, ‚Äédidn't she?

00:04:14.837 --> 00:04:16.547
‚ÄéWhy would you bring her up?

00:04:18.174 --> 00:04:19.008
‚ÄéJust you wait.

00:04:19.801 --> 00:04:21.719
‚ÄéI'll find Jang Eun-ju's body,

00:04:21.803 --> 00:04:23.513
‚Äéno matter how well you hid it.

00:04:23.596 --> 00:04:25.473
‚ÄéYou have quite the imagination.

00:04:27.058 --> 00:04:29.143
‚ÄéNice jacket. Looks good on you.

00:04:35.441 --> 00:04:36.901
‚ÄéGhosts tell you stuff?

00:04:36.985 --> 00:04:37.819
‚ÄéLike what?

00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:39.779
‚ÄéIt's nothing.

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:41.281
‚ÄéI was just joking.

00:04:41.364 --> 00:04:44.409
‚ÄéShaman Baek's suppression ritual ‚Äéto stop you from seeing things.

00:04:44.492 --> 00:04:45.368
‚ÄéDid it fail?

00:04:45.994 --> 00:04:46.995
‚ÄéOf course not.

00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:50.373
‚ÄéDon't you act rash.

00:04:51.457 --> 00:04:53.501
‚ÄéThere are eyes and ears everywhere.

00:04:54.168 --> 00:04:57.463
‚ÄéA strange rumor has been ‚Äégoing around already.

00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.507
‚ÄéWhat kind of rumor?

00:05:01.884 --> 00:05:03.011
‚ÄéThat you were ordained as a shaman.

00:05:04.804 --> 00:05:07.807
‚ÄéI assume it was your ex-fianc√©'s family ‚Äéwho started it.

00:05:08.808 --> 00:05:11.185
‚ÄéJust make sure ‚Äéyou don't get caught up in gossip.

00:05:12.478 --> 00:05:13.813
‚ÄéI'll be careful.

00:05:15.648 --> 00:05:16.482
‚ÄéOh, right.

00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:20.611
‚ÄéAbout the Competitiveness ‚ÄéImprovement Strategy.

00:05:20.695 --> 00:05:24.991
‚ÄéI thought you'd suggest ‚Äéwe drive Reina forward with an upgrade,

00:05:25.658 --> 00:05:27.618
‚Äéjust as luxury brands ‚Äéhave their high-end tier.

00:05:27.702 --> 00:05:30.872
‚ÄéReina Seoul will stick to the strategy ‚Äéto upgrade and improve.

00:05:30.955 --> 00:05:33.333
‚ÄéThe same goes ‚Äéfor the Busan and Gyeongju branches.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.794
‚ÄéBut if we consider the brand as a whole,

00:05:36.878 --> 00:05:39.255
‚Äéwe need a strategic revamp ‚Äéto change our structure.

00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:42.550
‚ÄéIt's not a decision ‚Äéto make here and now,

00:05:42.633 --> 00:05:44.761
‚Äébut I thought of CL Raymond Hotel.

00:05:45.428 --> 00:05:47.722
‚ÄéI find their brand strategy ‚Äéquite appealing.

00:05:48.306 --> 00:05:51.267
‚ÄéWhen CL Group opened their first hotel,

00:05:51.350 --> 00:05:56.064
‚Äéthey collaborated with Raymond, ‚Äéthe global hotel chain, to succeed.

00:05:57.315 --> 00:06:00.276
‚ÄéIt's true that global hotel chains ‚Äéare entering not only Seoul,

00:06:00.359 --> 00:06:02.570
‚Äébut other larger cities as well.

00:06:03.488 --> 00:06:06.741
‚ÄéStill, I'm against it. ‚ÄéWhy bother paying a fee to use a name?

00:06:08.076 --> 00:06:10.286
‚ÄéThey opened last year ‚Äéand you know how much they grew.

00:06:10.369 --> 00:06:11.454
‚ÄéIt's not a bad idea.

00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:13.247
‚ÄéGive it some thought.

00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:19.170
‚ÄéIt's me. Where about are you?

00:06:19.253 --> 00:06:21.422
‚ÄéWhere else? ‚ÄéI'm on my way back to the office.

00:06:22.006 --> 00:06:23.341
‚ÄéDidn't you take the day off?

00:06:23.424 --> 00:06:25.134
‚ÄéWhy would I take the day off?

00:06:25.718 --> 00:06:28.638
‚ÄéPeople like me don't have the time ‚Äéto take days off.

00:06:28.721 --> 00:06:31.974
‚ÄéI've reminded you so many times ‚Äésince last month.

00:06:32.058 --> 00:06:35.061
‚ÄéYou must do a good deed today ‚Äéduring the Hour of the Monkey.

00:06:35.144 --> 00:06:38.231
‚ÄéI'm not some high schooler ‚Äécollecting good deed miles for university.

00:06:38.314 --> 00:06:41.150
‚ÄéGood deeds only work out ‚Äéif they come from the heart.

00:06:41.651 --> 00:06:45.321
‚ÄéWhat's the point in doing good ‚Äéon an auspicious day just to avoid evil

00:06:45.404 --> 00:06:47.073
‚ÄéMy goodness.

00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:50.618
‚ÄéMy one and only grandson ‚Äédoesn't listen to a word I say.

00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:52.870
‚ÄéIf you think that little of me,

00:06:52.954 --> 00:06:55.289
‚ÄéI don't see the point ‚Äéin living any longer.

00:06:55.373 --> 00:06:56.958
‚ÄéI've outlived my welcome.

00:06:57.041 --> 00:07:00.044
‚ÄéCome on, don't say that. ‚ÄéYou're breaking your grandson's heart.

00:07:00.753 --> 00:07:02.463
‚ÄéI'm on my way, okay?

00:07:02.547 --> 00:07:04.006
‚ÄéI'll take the afternoon off.

00:07:21.941 --> 00:07:22.775
‚ÄéCareful, kids.

00:07:23.985 --> 00:07:25.403
‚ÄéYou said you wanted this last time.

00:07:25.486 --> 00:07:28.197
‚Äé-Be careful, guys. ‚Äé-It's mine!

00:07:28.281 --> 00:07:30.616
‚Äé-One, two, three, let's go! ‚Äé-Let's go!

00:07:33.536 --> 00:07:34.620
‚ÄéPass it forward.

00:07:34.704 --> 00:07:35.830
‚ÄéWe lost the ball!

00:07:42.545 --> 00:07:43.379
‚ÄéOh, no.

00:07:48.676 --> 00:07:51.053
‚Äé-No, don't lose it! ‚Äé-Get it!

00:07:51.137 --> 00:07:52.972
‚ÄéHey, no.

00:07:53.055 --> 00:07:54.390
‚ÄéFoul! That's a foul!

00:07:58.936 --> 00:08:01.981
‚Äé-You couldn't block that? ‚Äé-He aimed too well.

00:08:02.064 --> 00:08:04.108
‚Äé-No, it's just that ‚Äé-How did you miss it?

00:08:25.254 --> 00:08:27.298
‚Äé-That is bad. ‚Äé-Oh, no.

00:08:28.508 --> 00:08:31.093
‚ÄéWe replaced that window ‚Äéjust three days ago.

00:08:31.177 --> 00:08:33.304
‚ÄéThe director's away on business, right?

00:08:33.387 --> 00:08:34.388
‚ÄéYes, that's true.

00:08:34.972 --> 00:08:35.806
‚ÄéI'll destroy the evidence.

00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:38.643
‚ÄéThe director's office is locked ‚Äéand we don't have the key.

00:08:38.726 --> 00:08:39.977
‚ÄéThere's always a way.

00:08:40.811 --> 00:08:41.646
‚ÄéA way?

00:09:00.706 --> 00:09:01.832
‚ÄéI found the ball!

00:09:16.973 --> 00:09:20.351
‚ÄéPeople who stayed in the rooms near Jang's ‚Äéaround the time of her disappearance?

00:09:20.434 --> 00:09:22.687
‚ÄéYes, those who stayed in the rooms ‚Äénext to, above, and below hers,

00:09:22.770 --> 00:09:25.481
‚Äéthe times they checked in and out, ‚Äéand their alibis for that period.

00:09:25.982 --> 00:09:26.857
‚ÄéGot it.

00:09:28.192 --> 00:09:29.860
‚ÄéOkay.

00:09:31.612 --> 00:09:35.074
‚ÄéPark Seung-jae sunk thrilling shot ‚Äéafter shot at the championship

00:09:35.157 --> 00:09:38.119
‚Äéand is now top of the leaderboard ‚Äéin the third round.

00:09:39.829 --> 00:09:43.583
‚ÄéWow, you ripped the green ‚Äélike you were shredding a stage.

00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:46.377
‚ÄéThis is embarrassing. Let's just drink.

00:09:47.503 --> 00:09:49.422
‚ÄéMr. Park. You're pretty cool.

00:09:50.923 --> 00:09:52.592
‚ÄéThis is just between us,

00:09:52.675 --> 00:09:55.094
‚Äébut isn't that score a miracle ‚Äécompared to your previous games?

00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:59.932
‚ÄéI mean, data is science,

00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:02.351
‚Äébut what beats science is luck.

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:04.186
‚ÄéI guess I got a lucky break.

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:05.855
‚Äé-That's it. ‚Äé-Yeah, nice.

00:10:06.355 --> 00:10:07.523
‚Äé-Mom. ‚Äé-Yes?

00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:10.067
‚ÄéShould we ask Shaman Baek ‚Äéto write him a talisman

00:10:10.151 --> 00:10:12.361
‚Äéso his luck doesn't run out?

00:10:13.904 --> 00:10:14.739
‚ÄéWell

00:10:14.822 --> 00:10:17.742
‚ÄéWhy not? They say ghosts control luck.

00:10:17.825 --> 00:10:20.828
‚ÄéShaman Baek is best at handling spirits, ‚Äélike what he did for Yeo-ri.

00:10:20.911 --> 00:10:22.246
‚ÄéHa-ri.

00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:25.291
‚ÄéWas Ms. Cheon ever possessed by a ghost?

00:10:25.374 --> 00:10:26.667
‚ÄéGosh, no.

00:10:26.751 --> 00:10:28.544
‚ÄéShe wasn't possessed.

00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:31.505
‚ÄéShe's a ghost herself, ‚Äéthe type that drags others down.

00:10:31.589 --> 00:10:33.382
‚ÄéShe totally badmouthed you last time.

00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:35.009
‚ÄéMe? What did she say?

00:10:35.593 --> 00:10:36.469
‚ÄéWhat was it again?

00:10:37.261 --> 00:10:39.764
‚ÄéThat you dumped your ex for my money ‚Äéand that you're a parasite.

00:10:39.847 --> 00:10:40.973
‚ÄéHey, don't.

00:10:41.474 --> 00:10:43.517
‚ÄéWhat? She did say that.

00:10:45.269 --> 00:10:46.896
‚ÄéYou can't just barge in like that.

00:10:50.691 --> 00:10:51.525
‚ÄéWhat do you want?

00:10:55.071 --> 00:10:57.990
‚ÄéMs. Cheon, ‚ÄéI hear you've been talking reckless.

00:10:59.408 --> 00:11:02.036
‚ÄéThat I'm a parasite who dumped my ex

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:03.704
‚Äéfor Ha-ri's money.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:08.626
‚ÄéWhat was that smirk about?

00:11:10.461 --> 00:11:12.755
‚ÄéCheon Yeo-ri. Do you hate me that much?

00:11:12.838 --> 00:11:14.590
‚ÄéAm I not good enough for your cousin?

00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:17.885
‚ÄéNot good enough doesn't even cover it.

00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:20.554
‚ÄéThe truth is, Jang Eun-ju

00:11:21.680 --> 00:11:23.891
‚Äécame to our hotel before she went missing.

00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:28.562
‚ÄéHello, ma'am.

00:11:29.271 --> 00:11:31.273
‚ÄéI'll speak with her. Can you excuse us?

00:11:31.357 --> 00:11:32.274
‚ÄéYes, of course.

00:11:38.781 --> 00:11:40.491
‚ÄéYou want to reserve Siena Hall?

00:11:41.075 --> 00:11:42.076
‚ÄéYes.

00:11:42.159 --> 00:11:46.038
‚ÄéIs there a problem ‚Äéfor you to come see me in person?

00:11:46.122 --> 00:11:47.873
‚ÄéNo, there's no problem.

00:11:48.374 --> 00:11:51.252
‚ÄéIt's just that the name of your groom

00:11:52.002 --> 00:11:54.004
‚Äémade me wonder if it's the person

00:11:54.797 --> 00:11:56.048
‚ÄéI happen to know.

00:11:58.300 --> 00:11:59.677
‚ÄéYes, it's him.

00:12:01.178 --> 00:12:04.306
‚ÄéYou see, there's nothing else I can do,

00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:06.058
‚Äéso I had no choice but to come here.

00:12:09.228 --> 00:12:12.022
‚ÄéHe asked me to marry him ‚Äéand put this ring on my finger,

00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:15.568
‚Äébut then he broke up with me ‚Äéand started dating someone else.

00:12:20.448 --> 00:12:21.824
‚ÄéI'm pregnant.

00:12:25.619 --> 00:12:27.288
‚ÄéI can't live without Seung-jae.

00:12:29.123 --> 00:12:30.583
‚ÄéWill you please help me?

00:12:39.049 --> 00:12:40.551
‚ÄéWhat stupid crap is this?

00:12:41.051 --> 00:12:43.179
‚ÄéYou think she got pregnant ‚Äéjust from holding hands?

00:12:43.929 --> 00:12:46.056
‚Äé-You're saying it wasn't you? ‚Äé-Of course not!

00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:48.309
‚ÄéShe's a professional ‚Äéwhen it comes to bluffing and lying.

00:12:48.934 --> 00:12:50.686
‚ÄéYou don't believe what she said, do you?

00:12:51.312 --> 00:12:53.647
‚ÄéI guess the only way to find out

00:12:53.731 --> 00:12:55.232
‚Äéis to set up a three-way encounter.

00:12:55.816 --> 00:12:56.734
‚ÄéA three-way encounter?

00:12:57.401 --> 00:12:58.903
‚ÄéYou, me, and who else?

00:12:59.403 --> 00:13:00.237
‚ÄéJang Eun-ju.

00:13:02.198 --> 00:13:05.784
‚ÄéJust how would you sit ‚Äéface-to-face with the dead?

00:13:05.868 --> 00:13:08.954
‚ÄéYou said she wasn't dead, but in hiding.

00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:10.998
‚ÄéWasn't that the story you told?

00:13:12.416 --> 00:13:15.377
‚ÄéWell, yes. She disappeared.

00:13:16.337 --> 00:13:17.713
‚ÄéIf something feels off,

00:13:17.796 --> 00:13:20.466
‚Äéisn't it best to cover all bases?

00:13:20.549 --> 00:13:22.259
‚ÄéLet's go for a three-way encounter.

00:13:32.186 --> 00:13:35.731
‚ÄéSo you're saying ‚ÄéJang Eun-ju is coming here?

00:13:38.817 --> 00:13:39.902
‚ÄéShe could be here already.

00:13:42.613 --> 00:13:43.781
‚ÄéCome on in.

00:13:56.460 --> 00:13:58.045
‚ÄéIs there anything that seems off?

00:13:58.671 --> 00:13:59.505
‚ÄéNot yet.

00:14:00.422 --> 00:14:01.298
‚ÄéWhat about the call history?

00:14:01.382 --> 00:14:03.342
‚ÄéI didn't find much from that either,

00:14:03.425 --> 00:14:05.261
‚Äéother than what we mentioned ‚Äéin the previous trial.

00:14:05.344 --> 00:14:08.514
‚ÄéI don't think we'll find anything new.

00:14:10.558 --> 00:14:13.978
‚ÄéEvil is thorough and meticulous, ‚Äéso it stays well-hidden.

00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:17.481
‚ÄéWe must find something ‚Äéwe might have overlooked.

00:14:17.565 --> 00:14:19.817
‚ÄéSomething to overturn the verdict ‚Äéin the second trial.

00:14:19.900 --> 00:14:20.985
‚ÄéA smoking gun.

00:14:21.068 --> 00:14:23.279
‚ÄéWell, the best smoking gun would be

00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:33.163
‚ÄéJang Eun-ju's discarded body.

00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:45.467
‚ÄéYou asked for me?

00:14:48.679 --> 00:14:50.890
‚ÄéMr. Park will be on his way out.

00:14:50.973 --> 00:14:53.058
‚ÄéMake sure to give him ‚Äésome free merchandise.

00:14:53.851 --> 00:14:55.269
‚ÄéYes, ma'am.

00:14:58.314 --> 00:15:00.357
‚ÄéYour secretary is Jang Eun-ju?

00:15:00.441 --> 00:15:02.026
‚ÄéYou already knew

00:15:03.027 --> 00:15:06.113
‚Äéthere was no way Jang Eun-ju ‚Äéwould walk through that door.

00:15:08.324 --> 00:15:10.492
‚ÄéYou have a way of cornering someone.

00:15:11.327 --> 00:15:12.828
‚ÄéWe'll be in-laws soon, you know.

00:15:14.455 --> 00:15:15.372
‚ÄéBy the way,

00:15:15.873 --> 00:15:17.666
‚ÄéEun-ju asked me to tell you this.

00:15:20.586 --> 00:15:23.589
‚ÄéShe hopes you win this championship.

00:15:23.672 --> 00:15:25.382
‚Äé-What? ‚Äé-She says

00:15:26.091 --> 00:15:29.219
‚Äéthe higher you are, the harder the fall.

00:15:31.055 --> 00:15:32.181
‚ÄéI'm rooting for you

00:15:32.848 --> 00:15:34.391
‚Äéand your most monumental fall.

00:15:35.142 --> 00:15:36.936
‚ÄéMonumental fall, my ass.

00:15:53.285 --> 00:15:54.328
‚Äé-Wait. ‚Äé-What?

00:15:57.748 --> 00:16:00.042
‚Äé-I've seen her somewhere. ‚Äé-Where?

00:16:09.760 --> 00:16:10.594
‚ÄéThere.

00:16:14.348 --> 00:16:16.517
‚ÄéThe woman in the photo ‚Äéon Park Seung-jae's phone.

