00:52:41.575 --> 00:52:45.120
‚ÄéThat was the first friend I invited ‚Äésince opening the hotel.

00:52:45.203 --> 00:52:46.830
‚ÄéHow incompetent do you think I looked?

00:52:47.747 --> 00:52:50.458
‚ÄéYou see, that actually hurt my pride.

00:52:51.585 --> 00:52:52.460
‚ÄéI'm sorry, sir.

00:52:52.544 --> 00:52:56.506
‚ÄéCould you find it within yourself ‚Äéto show some mercy and lenience?

00:53:01.386 --> 00:53:02.304
‚ÄéLet's do this then.

00:53:03.471 --> 00:53:07.100
‚ÄéResign from our hotel, ‚Äéand I'll find you a job at another one.

00:53:08.310 --> 00:53:09.603
‚ÄéThe same goes for the young man.

00:53:14.524 --> 00:53:16.610
‚ÄéI'm here to see my granddaughter.

00:53:16.693 --> 00:53:20.739
‚ÄéShe used to work at this company, ‚Äéand she said she'd be here today.

00:53:20.822 --> 00:53:22.991
‚Äé-Da-mi, where are you? ‚Äé-Take a seat, ma'am.

00:53:23.074 --> 00:53:25.285
‚Äé-We should get someone. ‚Äé-Your grandma's here.

00:53:25.368 --> 00:53:26.578
‚ÄéDa-mi!

00:53:26.661 --> 00:53:28.079
‚ÄéWe need you to leave.

00:53:28.163 --> 00:53:30.332
‚Äé-Da-mi, where are you? ‚Äé-Excuse me.

00:53:30.415 --> 00:53:31.833
‚Äé-Where ‚Äé-Give me a minute.

00:53:33.293 --> 00:53:34.836
‚ÄéYou're Grandma Chun-hui, right?

00:53:34.920 --> 00:53:37.172
‚ÄéMy goodness, aren't you Prosecutor Ma?

00:53:37.255 --> 00:53:38.882
‚ÄéI was afraid I wouldn't get to see you.

00:53:39.758 --> 00:53:41.384
‚ÄéWhat's the matter?

00:53:43.386 --> 00:53:44.429
‚ÄéProsecutor Ma.

00:53:48.558 --> 00:53:52.520
‚ÄéYou reported that your granddaughter Da-mi ‚Äédidn't come home last night,

00:53:52.604 --> 00:53:54.981
‚Äébut the police thinks ‚Äéshe ran away from home?

00:53:56.358 --> 00:53:58.318
‚ÄéBut you remembered her saying ‚Äébefore she left

00:53:58.401 --> 00:54:01.947
‚Äéthat she'd attend the fashion show ‚Äébeing held at this hotel,

00:54:02.030 --> 00:54:03.907
‚Äé-so you came to look for her? ‚Äé-That's right.

00:54:04.574 --> 00:54:06.326
‚ÄéShe won't answer her phone.

00:54:06.409 --> 00:54:09.329
‚ÄéI'm dead worried ‚Äésomething happened to her.

00:54:10.330 --> 00:54:13.500
‚ÄéShe'd been acting strange ‚Äéthe past few days.

00:54:13.583 --> 00:54:16.711
‚ÄéDid she say anything about meeting anyone?

00:54:16.795 --> 00:54:17.963
‚ÄéShe only said

00:54:18.046 --> 00:54:21.633
‚Äéshe was going to the hotel ‚Äéto see someone's event.

00:54:22.509 --> 00:54:23.468
‚ÄéProsecutor Ma.

00:54:23.551 --> 00:54:27.097
‚ÄéWill you please find Da-mi for me?

00:54:30.600 --> 00:54:33.144
‚ÄéCould I take a look around her room?

00:54:35.230 --> 00:54:36.272
‚ÄéCome on in.

00:54:44.489 --> 00:54:45.949
‚ÄéTake all the time you need.

00:54:46.032 --> 00:54:47.367
‚ÄéI'll get you something to eat.

00:55:38.918 --> 00:55:41.463
‚ÄéGosh, why did the car brake ‚Äéall of a sudden?

00:55:41.546 --> 00:55:42.839
‚ÄéI'm sorry, ma'am.

00:55:43.965 --> 00:55:45.508
‚ÄéIt's fine.

00:56:02.942 --> 00:56:03.985
‚ÄéI have a favor to ask.

00:56:05.153 --> 00:56:07.489
‚ÄéSkim through it fast. Thanks.

00:56:07.572 --> 00:56:10.950
‚ÄéCan I see the footage ‚Äéfrom that camera too?

00:56:11.785 --> 00:56:12.827
‚ÄéYou've been at it for an hour.

00:56:13.495 --> 00:56:15.163
‚ÄéDidn't you say you wouldn't be long?

00:56:15.246 --> 00:56:18.166
‚ÄéYou acted so magnanimous earlier, ‚Äéthat I could call at any time.

00:56:19.959 --> 00:56:21.169
‚ÄéCan we go forward from here?

00:56:21.252 --> 00:56:22.796
‚ÄéA bit more.

00:56:22.879 --> 00:56:23.880
‚ÄéMore.

00:56:23.963 --> 00:56:24.964
‚ÄéGo further.

00:56:25.965 --> 00:56:26.883
‚ÄéStop!

00:56:27.634 --> 00:56:28.468
‚ÄéRight there.

00:56:28.551 --> 00:56:30.095
‚ÄéRewind just a bit from here.

00:56:30.678 --> 00:56:32.347
‚ÄéJust a bit. A bit more.

00:56:34.808 --> 00:56:37.102
‚ÄéThat's it. Now skim right ahead.

00:56:37.977 --> 00:56:40.105
‚ÄéKeep going. Keep on going.

00:56:40.188 --> 00:56:41.397
‚ÄéMore. A bit more.

00:56:42.398 --> 00:56:43.274
‚ÄéA bit more.

00:56:44.526 --> 00:56:45.401
‚ÄéRight there.

00:56:46.319 --> 00:56:47.654
‚ÄéZoom into that shot.

00:56:48.655 --> 00:56:50.323
‚ÄéOur cameras don't have that function.

00:56:50.406 --> 00:56:51.241
‚ÄéThey don't?

00:56:51.324 --> 00:56:53.284
‚ÄéThis isn't one of your offices.

00:56:53.952 --> 00:56:55.453
‚ÄéCan you please leave now?

00:56:56.496 --> 00:56:57.956
‚ÄéI saw all I needed. Thank you.

00:56:58.039 --> 00:56:58.873
‚ÄéSure.

00:57:05.130 --> 00:57:08.633
‚ÄéI located the taxi ‚Äéand emailed you the details.

00:57:08.716 --> 00:57:11.261
‚ÄéI asked the local police ‚Äéfor assistance too.

00:57:11.344 --> 00:57:12.887
‚ÄéCan you tell me what's going on?

00:57:12.971 --> 00:57:14.055
‚ÄéAll right.

00:57:14.139 --> 00:57:15.974
‚ÄéI'll call you back in a bit.

00:57:51.551 --> 00:57:53.845
‚ÄéThis is where the taxi dropped her off.

00:57:57.307 --> 00:57:58.641
‚ÄéWhat is that woman doing down there?

00:58:18.077 --> 00:58:19.704
‚Äé-Excuse me? ‚Äé-Oh, shoot.

00:58:22.248 --> 00:58:25.001
‚ÄéLife is very precious ‚Äéif you think about it.

00:58:26.294 --> 00:58:27.128
‚ÄéHuh?

00:58:28.505 --> 00:58:30.965
‚ÄéWhat are you doing here this time?

00:58:31.591 --> 00:58:33.843
‚ÄéDid you have to make me jump like that?

00:58:34.427 --> 00:58:36.971
‚ÄéWhat are you doing here on your own, ‚Äélooking all gloomy?

00:58:37.055 --> 00:58:38.389
‚ÄéIt's nothing.

00:58:38.890 --> 00:58:40.266
‚ÄéDon't mind me.

00:58:40.892 --> 00:58:42.018
‚ÄéJust go on your way.

01:00:50.480 --> 01:00:52.899
‚ÄéSPOOKY IN LOVE

01:00:53.816 --> 01:00:56.069
‚ÄéI just can't seem to make sense of it.

01:00:56.152 --> 01:00:58.112
‚ÄéHow did you know where to go?

